The South African National Youth Orchestra Summer Concert is on at 7.30pm today at ZK Matthews Great Hall Unisa. Tickets cost R280 and are available at Computicket. For more information contact Sophia on 0832722117 or e-mail sophia@sanyo.org.za.  Saturday Friends of the Rail steam train departs from FOTR Depot, Hermanstad, at 8am for Cullinan tomorrow. Spend the day exploring Cullinan village before going home at 3.15pm. Braai fires will be provided next to the station, go on a mine tour, have lunch at one of the restaurants, visit museums and craft shops etc. Bookings close at noon today, book at Checkers, Shoprite Moneymarkets or Computicket. Call 012 767 7913 or 0820986186.  Sunday Caiphus Semenya and Letta Mbulu will be performing live on stage, at the South African State Theatre, on Sunday at 3pm. Tickets range between R150 and R300 and are available at Computicket. For more information call 012 392 4000.  Shows Vibrant production of Aladdin at Irene Village Theatre, in a show that ends tomorrow. Tickets are available at Computicket and range between R85 and R100. For more information call 0848040490 or e-mail tshwaneyouththeatre@gmail.com   Cinderella on Ice show will be showing at Teatro at Montecasino Theatre until January 6. Performances: Tuesdays to Fridays at 7.30pm, Saturdays, 3pm and 7.30pm, Sundays at 2pm and 5.30pm. Tickets available at Computicket.com. For more information visit www.imperialicestars.com.   Markets Friday@theCollection is on every Friday from 5pm to 9pm at The Collection at 5 Boendoe Avenue, Garsfontein. For more information call 012 933 3638 or visit www.thecollection.co.za.  The Boeremark market opens at 5.30am until 9.30am at Moreleta Street tomorrow in Silverton. Call: 0798971025.  Hazel Food Market is also on, tomorrow from 8am to 2pm at the corner of Thomas Edison and Mackenzie streets, Menlo Park; the last market for 2017 will be on December 23. For more information contact Gerhard Scholtz on 078 583 7716.  Greenlyn Village in Menlo Park also has its Greenlyn Goods Market tomorrow from 8am to 2pm. Call: 0823733517.  Christmas Market at Wimpy Court, Kolonnade Retail Park, tomorrow from 8am to 2pm. Putt-putt and play area until December 18. Children to play under parents’ supervision. For more information call 012 548 0666.  The Irene Green Market is open, and tomorrow it is on from 9am at Jan Smuts House Museum in Irene. Call: 0825535044.  The Cowhouse Market is on every Saturday and Sunday from 10am to 10pm, at Cowhouse Market in Hazeldean. Call James Waugh on 072 3990154.  The Tshwane Christmas Festival is on at Freedom Park: come and enjoy a wonderful Christmas Market with a delightful clamber club kiddies area. There will be Carols by Candlelight, food and drink stalls and Christmas lights to bring festive cheer to the whole family. The market will run until December 30 and it starts at 3pm and runs until 10pm. Tickets pre-sold at Computicket or at the gate on the day. R80 adults, R30 for kids and free entry for under 2s. For more information contact Lydia Ngake at 0123270046 or e-mail lydia@productionprojects.co.za.  Christmas Events Visit the Magical Snow Booth at Quagga Mall, cnr Nkomo and Quagga streets, Pretoria West, until December 24. Bring the family and experience a magical place this festive season and discover our snow booth. Entrance is free, snow trading hours are Monday to Friday from 10am to 4pm, and on Saturday from 10am to 3pm and on Sunday and holidays from 10am to 2pm. For more 
information call 012 327 2295.  A Festival of Nine Lessons and Carols at Christ Church Arcadia (820 Pretorius Street) on Christmas Eve (December 24) at 5.30pm. The 37th annual carol service for the whole family with the customary mix of old and new. Music is directed by George King with Willie Steyn on the organ. It includes Christmas music by Gabriel Jackson, John Joubert, William Mathias and William Walton, with carol arrangements by David Willcocks and George King. Enquiries: 083 306 4478.  Home Grown Holidays, Santa’s workshop at Food Court Wonderpark Mall is on until December 31; Monday to Friday from 9am to 6pm; Saturday from 9am to 4pm and Sunday from 9am to 2pm. For more information call 012 549 1690.  Arts Eric Bolsmann’s unique exhibition of a series of 23 oil paintings of Pretoria of the 1860s to 1900s continues at the 20/20 Gallery at the Voortrekker Monument Heritage site. It is running until December 18. Call: 012 362 6698.  For the Diary Vintage and Classic Car Display is on every Saturday from 9am at Shop 27 next to Puma, Kolonnade Retail Park. For more information contact Frik Kraamwinkel on 082 444 2954.  Annual New Year festival on January 1, at the Ditsong Pioneer Museum, Silverton. Traditional festival will start at 10am. Entrance fees: R30 per adult & student; R20 per senior citizen; R10 per child between 3 and 6 years, R25 per child between 7 and 18 years and free entry for children under 3. For more information contact 0128138006.